				<h3>What is the difference between private and group instruction??</h3>
				<img src="/images/dav2private.jpg" align="right" height="205" width="200" />
				<p align="left"><span>Private Instruction</span> is best for golfers who have been playing awhile and may have developed problems specific to themselves, requiring an individual improvement plan and coaching or for those just starting out who may feel uncomfortable in a group setting or simply want the instructors individual attention.<br /> <br /> <img src="/images/dave2group.jpg" alt="Group Lessons" height="165" width="400" /></p>
				<p><span>Group Instruction or Clinics</span> are ideal for those golfers who have the same needs or interests and therefore will be getting the same information, for example: Beginners, Juniors, Ladies, Corporate Outings, Golf Schools, Business Leagues or when the instruction is concentrated on one specific subject, for example: Chipping, Driving, Sand Shots Putting. The main advantage for group instruction or clinics is the lower cost.</p>
